<p>Classified as a Large Urban Park (designed to meet community-based recreational needs and preservation of unique landscapes and open space), Riverside is the largest park in the Grand Rapids parks system, aside from Aman Park (331 acres) which is outside the city limits. The park has bike and walking paths along the river, lagoons for fishing and nature study, boat launching ramps, ball diamonds, frisbee golf courses, and is host to many community festivals and events.</p>
