<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">In 1954 the Board of Education received a portion of Fuller Park in order to build a school.&nbsp; Hillcrest School was included in the new school-park plan, and eventually Hillcrest Park became a park of its own.&nbsp; In 2004, citizens raised funds to build a dog park on the site to be opened the following year.&nbsp; It is still the only official dog park in the City.<br /></span></p>|, latitude: 42.9669, longitude: -85.6353, park_size: 14.43, address: %Q|1415 Lyon NE Grand Rapids|, vimeo_embed: %Q||, flickr_pool: %Q|1238780@N25|},
