<p>The open, hard-surface plaza adjoining the City and County buildings  hosts numerous large community events and "La Grand Vitesse," the  Alexander Calder Stabile which symbolizes the City of Grand Rapids.</p>
<p>It is the first public sculpture in America to be jointly funded by a federal grant and private dollars, including a $45,000 National Endowment of the Arts grant.&nbsp; Local resident Nancy Mulnix was responsible for bringing the stabile to Grand Rapids, and is known as the "mother of the calder."</p>|, latitude: 42.969, longitude: -85.6711, park_size: 4.43, address: %Q|300 Monroe NW Grand Rapids|, vimeo_embed: %Q||, flickr_pool: %Q|1289893@N21|},
