<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;"><br />Local sculptor joseph Kinnebrew's Grand River Sculpture was heralded as the "marrieage of arts of environmental concerns." and allows people to engage with the fish run in an architecturally disesigned space.&nbsp; Costing $90,000, many agencies, including the National Endowment of the Arts provided funding for the walkupon sculpture.&nbsp; In 1976, it was awarded the Michigan Week Community Achievement of the Year Award, the first ever for sculpture.</p>|, latitude: 42.9747, longitude: -85.6764, park_size: 3.4, address: %Q|606 Front NW Grand Rapids|, vimeo_embed: %Q||, flickr_pool: %Q|1321127@N22|},
