{id: 40, name: %Q|Rosa Park Circle|, history: %Q|<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">This park has become the heart and soul of the city.&nbsp; The park was originally named Monroe Mall Amphitheater but is now named Rosa Parks Circle in honor of the famous Michigan resident Rosa Parks.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">The unique park was created by Maya Lin as a functioning sculpture that could support as a local venue for special events and gatherings.&nbsp; It is made up of a 13000 sq/ft oval amphitheater "Ecliptic", 166 fiber-optic lights, trees, two reflective pools and a statue of Rosa herself.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;">&nbsp;</p>
