<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;"><br />Funding from the Works Progress Administration (WPA) was used to improve the land as an athletic field. For years Valley Field was home to local baseball clubs such as the American Seating Co. team, the Seaters.&nbsp; On July 28, 1996, Valley Field was named Sullivan Field in honor of longtime local amateur baseball sponsor and entrepreneur, Bob Sullivan.</p>|, latitude: 42.9772, longitude: -85.7006, park_size: 5.5, address: %Q|700 Valley Ave NW Grand Rapids|, vimeo_embed: %Q||, flickr_pool: %Q||},
