{id: 46, name: %Q|Burton Woods|, history: %Q|<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;">est. 1914 - donation</p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Natural area adjacent to Garfield Park. </span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">The woods was part of the farm that Charles Garfield's father purchased from the Burtons in 1856.&nbsp; Garfield set aside six acres for planting a variety of trees after the Detroit, Lansing and Northern Railroad cut a swath through his land in 1892.&nbsp; Garfield donated these acres to the city for a park.&nbsp; In the 1960s, residents fought a City Commission decision to sell the land, and after continued pressure, the matter was dropped in 1969.<br /></span></p>|, latitude: 42.9231, longitude: -85.6625, park_size: 5.97, address: %Q|2259 Everest SE Grand Rapids|, vimeo_embed: %Q||, flickr_pool: %Q||},
