{id: 74, name: %Q|Campau Park |, history: %Q|<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">An 1899 gift to the City from Marton Antoine Ryerson, the park was originally named Antoine Campau's farm. &nbsp;An uncle to Ryerson, Campau was a brother to the city's early settler, Louis Campau. &nbsp;In 1955, the board of education purchased adjoining properties for an elementary school. &nbsp;A portion of Ryerson Street was vacated, and Campau Park School was established.</span></p>|, latitude: 42.9474, longitude: -85.6691, park_size: 7.27, address: %Q|50 Antoine SW Grand Rapids|, vimeo_embed: %Q||, flickr_pool: %Q||},
