<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">A gift of George A. Rumsey in March 1911, Rumsey Park was originally intended to act as a buffer between the industry along Godfrey Ave. and the residential areato the east. On September 11, 1983, Rumsey Park officially became Clemente Park in honor of the late Pittsburgh Pirate, Roberto Clemente.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Recently, a citizens group has been working to raise funds to build a skate park on the former tennis courts.<br /></span></p>|, latitude: 42.9497, longitude: -85.6814, park_size: 11.91, address: %Q|546 Rumsey SW Grand Rapids|, vimeo_embed: %Q||, flickr_pool: %Q||},
{id: 77, name: %Q|Heartside Park|, history: %Q|<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;"><span style="letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Classified as a Neighborhood Park it serves as the recreational and social focus of the neighborhood. &nbsp;</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0.0px 0.0px 10.0px 0.0px; font: 10.0px Verdana;">Formally occupied by railroad tracks and a rail yard, the site's conversion to a park arose when Catholic Centrail High School eyed it for a playground and soccer field.&nbsp; That idea dispersed in 1995, but residents continued to advance the idea for a park.&nbsp; The park was dedicated in 2004.</p>
